      <section class="section" id="typography">
        <p class="eyebrow">03 — Typography</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Typography <a class="anchor" href="#typography" aria-label="Copy link to section">#</a></h2>
        <p class="lede">The IBM Plex super-family — one family carrying the brand across roles and languages.</p>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 1</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Why this family</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="note">We use one type family for everything: <strong>IBM Plex</strong>. It's a free, open-source family made by IBM, with matching styles for regular text, for code, and for Arabic script.</p>
        <p class="note">It fits us because it feels both technical and human — clean and precise, but still friendly. Using one family everywhere keeps the whole brand looking like it belongs together, from a business card to a product screen.</p>

        <div class="card card-pad typeface">
          <div class="type-hero">
            <div class="type-hero-glyph">Aa</div>
            <div class="type-hero-info">
              <div class="label">IBM Plex Sans</div>
              <p>The main typeface — for display, headings, body copy, and interface text.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="glyphset">
            <div class="glyph-row">ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ</div>
            <div class="glyph-row">abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz</div>
            <div class="glyph-row muted">0123456789 &amp; . , : ; ! ? — ( ) “ ” @ # % *</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card card-pad typeface">
          <div class="type-hero">
            <div class="type-hero-glyph mono">Aa</div>
            <div class="type-hero-info">
              <div class="label">IBM Plex Mono</div>
              <p>For code, data, version tags, and the brand's signature eyebrows and labels.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="glyphset">
            <div class="glyph-row mono">ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ</div>
            <div class="glyph-row mono">abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz</div>
            <div class="glyph-row mono muted">0123456789 &amp; . , : ; ! ? — ( ) &lt;/&gt; @ # % *</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card card-pad typeface">
          <div class="type-hero">
            <div class="type-hero-glyph arabic">اب</div>
            <div class="type-hero-info">
              <div class="label">IBM Plex Sans Arabic</div>
              <p>The same family for Central Kurdish &amp; Arabic (RTL), so both scripts read as one system with English.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="glyphset">
            <div class="glyph-row arabic">ا ب ت ث ج ح خ د ذ ر ز س ش ص ض ط ظ ع غ ف ق ك ل م ن ه و ي</div>
            <div class="glyph-row arabic">پ چ ژ ڤ گ ک ڕ ڵ ۆ ێ ە ھ ی</div>
            <div class="glyph-row arabic muted">٠ ١ ٢ ٣ ٤ ٥ ٦ ٧ ٨ ٩ — 0123456789</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 2</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Four roles, one family</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="note">Four jobs, one family. Everything is IBM Plex — only the cut and weight change with the role, so the brand always looks related.</p>
