      <!-- Tone & Voice -->
      <section class="section" id="tone-voice">
        <p class="eyebrow">04 — Tone &amp; Voice</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Tone &amp; Voice <a class="anchor" href="#tone-voice" aria-label="Copy link to section">#</a></h2>
        <p class="lede">We write like the product we ship — precise, warm, and human. Clear enough for a busy CTO, friendly enough that they actually want to reply.</p>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 1</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Personality</h3>
        </div>

        <p class="subhead">Five traits, one voice</p>
        <p class="note">The brand traits aren't decoration — they're how we choose words. Technical and bold give us confidence; approachable and curious keep us human; visionary keeps us looking forward.</p>
        <div class="traits">
          <div class="card card-pad personality">
            <h4 class="p-name">Technical</h4>
            <p class="p-desc">We know the craft and we're specific about it — comfortable with the detail.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad personality">
            <h4 class="p-name">Approachable</h4>
            <p class="p-desc">Easy to talk to. We meet people where they are and write to be understood.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad personality">
            <h4 class="p-name">Bold</h4>
            <p class="p-desc">Definite statements, standing behind the work — sure without being loud.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad personality">
            <h4 class="p-name">Visionary</h4>
            <p class="p-desc">Always looking forward — to where the product, and the client, are headed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad personality">
            <h4 class="p-name">Curious</h4>
            <p class="p-desc">We ask sharp questions and stay close to the problem worth solving.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 2</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Voice &amp; tone</h3>
        </div>

        <p class="subhead">Four rules that never flex</p>
        <p class="note">Tone changes with context; these four hold everywhere. When a sentence feels off, it's usually breaking one of them.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card card-pad principle">
            <span class="pr-num">01</span>
            <h4 class="pr-title">Clear over clever</h4>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark do">Do</span> Say exactly what something does. Lead with the point.</p>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark dont">Don't</span> Hide meaning behind jargon or wordplay.</p>
            <div class="pr-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “We architect bespoke digital ecosystems.”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “We design and build apps for your business.”</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card card-pad principle">
            <span class="pr-num">02</span>
            <h4 class="pr-title">Confident, not loud</h4>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark do">Do</span> Make definite statements; back them with specifics.</p>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark dont">Don't</span> Shout in superlatives and exclamation marks.</p>
            <div class="pr-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “The most revolutionary dev team in the world!!”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “We ship enterprise-grade products, on time.”</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card card-pad principle">
            <span class="pr-num">03</span>
            <h4 class="pr-title">Warm &amp; human</h4>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark do">Do</span> Talk to one person. Use “you” and contractions.</p>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark dont">Don't</span> Sound like a press release or a robot.</p>
            <div class="pr-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “Users may submit inquiries via the form.”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “Got a project in mind? Tell us about it.”</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card card-pad principle">
            <span class="pr-num">04</span>
            <h4 class="pr-title">Tailored &amp; specific</h4>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark do">Do</span> Speak to the exact situation; pick precise words.</p>
            <p class="pr-rule"><span class="pr-mark dont">Don't</span> Fall back on vague, one-size-fits-all filler.</p>
            <div class="pr-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “We offer a wide range of solutions.”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “We'll scope it, design it, build it, and launch it.”</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="subhead">Tone spectrum — same voice, different volume</p>
        <p class="note">Dial tone to the moment. A payment error wants calm and plain; a homepage wants bold and visionary. The personality stays constant — the volume moves.</p>
        <div class="spectrum">
          <div class="spectrum-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="spectrum-grid">
            <div class="sp-col"><div class="sp-ctx">Errors</div><div class="sp-tone">calm · plain</div></div>
            <div class="sp-col"><div class="sp-ctx">Product UI</div><div class="sp-tone">clear · functional</div></div>
            <div class="sp-col"><div class="sp-ctx">Proposals</div><div class="sp-tone">precise · confident</div></div>
            <div class="sp-col"><div class="sp-ctx">Marketing</div><div class="sp-tone">bold · visionary</div></div>
            <div class="sp-col"><div class="sp-ctx">Social</div><div class="sp-tone">sharp · curious</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="spectrum-ends"><span>Calm · functional</span><span>Expressive · bold</span></div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 3</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Vocabulary</h3>
        </div>

        <p class="subhead">Say this, not that</p>
        <p class="note">A short, opinionated word list. The left set sounds like us; the right set is industry filler we steer clear of.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card card-pad">
            <div class="vocab-head use">Words we use</div>
            <div class="chips">
              <span class="chip-use">build</span><span class="chip-use">ship</span><span class="chip-use">design</span><span class="chip-use">tailor</span><span class="chip-use">craft</span><span class="chip-use">partner</span><span class="chip-use">scope</span><span class="chip-use">scale</span><span class="chip-use">precise</span><span class="chip-use">launch</span><span class="chip-use">product</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad">
            <div class="vocab-head avoid">Words we avoid</div>
            <div class="chips">
              <span class="chip-avoid">synergy</span><span class="chip-avoid">leverage</span><span class="chip-avoid">cutting-edge</span><span class="chip-avoid">world-class</span><span class="chip-avoid">revolutionary</span><span class="chip-avoid">game-changer</span><span class="chip-avoid">seamless</span><span class="chip-avoid">disrupt</span><span class="chip-avoid">ninja / rockstar</span><span class="chip-avoid">just / simply</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 4</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Mechanics</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subhead">The small, consistent stuff</p>
        <p class="note">Our house style — the little rules that keep every sentence feeling like the same brand, in product and in marketing.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Capitalization</div>
            <p>Capitalize only the first word and any names — in headings, buttons, and labels. Don't capitalize every word, and avoid all-caps in body text.</p>
            <div class="mech-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “Start a project”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “Start A Project”</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Contractions</div>
            <p>Use them — we're, you'll, it's. They keep the tone human.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Numbers</div>
            <p>Numerals in UI and data; spell out one–nine in flowing prose.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Active voice</div>
            <p>Write in active voice, second person.</p>
            <div class="mech-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “You'll get a link.”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “Clients will be provided a link.”</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Buttons</div>
            <p>Start with a verb; say what happens.</p>
            <div class="mech-ex">
              <p class="pr-ex-yes"><span>✓</span> “Start a project”</p>
              <p class="pr-ex-no"><span>✗</span> “Submit”</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Exclamation marks</div>
            <p>One is a treat, not a habit — earn it. Let the words carry the energy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 5</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">In practice</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subhead">Before &amp; after</p>
        <p class="note">The same message, rewritten into the voice. Notice it gets shorter, clearer, and more human every time.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card card-pad ba">
            <div class="label">Homepage hero</div>
            <div class="ba-row before"><span class="ba-tag">Before</span><p>A world-class software agency leveraging cutting-edge technologies to deliver innovative solutions.</p></div>
            <div class="ba-row after"><span class="ba-tag">After</span><p>We design and build digital products, tailored to your business — concept to launch.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad ba">
            <div class="label">Call to action</div>
            <div class="ba-row before"><span class="ba-tag">Before</span><p>Submit your information</p></div>
            <div class="ba-row after"><span class="ba-tag">After</span><p>Start your project</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad ba">
            <div class="label">Error message</div>
            <div class="ba-row before"><span class="ba-tag">Before</span><p>Error: invalid input detected.</p></div>
            <div class="ba-row after"><span class="ba-tag">After</span><p>That email doesn't look right — mind checking it?</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad ba">
            <div class="label">Empty state</div>
            <div class="ba-row before"><span class="ba-tag">Before</span><p>No data available.</p></div>
            <div class="ba-row after"><span class="ba-tag">After</span><p>Nothing here yet. Create your first project to get going.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 6</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Bilingual voice</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subhead">Carrying the voice into Arabic &amp; Kurdish</p>
        <p class="note">Clarity and warmth translate; idioms don't. Adapt for meaning and rhythm, not word-for-word.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Transcreate, don't translate</div>
            <p>Adapt taglines and headlines with native speakers — match the feeling, not the literal phrasing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Mind the register</div>
            <p>Business Arabic and Kurdish read more formal. Keep our clarity and warmth; ease off very casual phrasing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Names stay in Latin</div>
            <p>Keep product and brand names in Latin script unless a localized form is agreed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad mech">
            <div class="label">Follow the type rules</div>
            <p>Apply the RTL, line-height, and numeral rules from the Typography foundation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 7</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">In the voice</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subhead">Boilerplate &amp; one-liner</p>
        <p class="note">Reference copy you can lift — written to the rules above. Treat it as a starting point, not gospel.</p>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card card-pad">
            <div class="label" style="margin-bottom:12px;">Boilerplate</div>
            <p style="margin:0 0 12px;">Tailored Applications is a company that designs and builds web and mobile apps for enterprise and growing businesses — from first concept to launch.</p>
            <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);">We bring together local and international talent to ship work that meets a global standard, tailored to each client's needs rather than forced through a template.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad oneliner">
            <div class="label" style="margin-bottom:12px;">One-liner</div>
            <p>Custom digital products, tailored to your business — concept to launch.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="part">
          <span class="part-num">Section 8</span>
          <h3 class="part-title">Guardrails</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subhead">Do &amp; don't</p>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card card-pad">
            <div class="vocab-head use">Do</div>
            <ul class="gr-list do">
              <li>Lead with the point; cut every word that isn't working.</li>
              <li>Write to one person, in active voice.</li>
              <li>Match tone to the moment along the spectrum.</li>
              <li>Be specific — name the thing, the step, the outcome.</li>
              <li>Sound confident by being concrete.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-pad">
            <div class="vocab-head avoid">Don't</div>
            <ul class="gr-list dont">
              <li>Reach for buzzwords or industry filler.</li>
              <li>Hype with superlatives and exclamation marks.</li>
              <li>Write like a press release or a legal notice.</li>
              <li>Blame the user in errors, or over-apologize.</li>
              <li>Translate idioms word-for-word across languages.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Coming soon -->
      <section class="section" id="patterns">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--coming);">Patterns</h2>
        <div class="soon-block"><span class="badge">Coming soon</span><div>This section will be added in a later phase.</div></div>
      </section>
      <section class="section" id="illustration">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--coming);">Illustration</h2>
        <div class="soon-block"><span class="badge">Coming soon</span><div>This section will be added in a later phase.</div></div>
      </section>
      <section class="section" id="photography">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--coming);">Photography</h2>
        <div class="soon-block"><span class="badge">Coming soon</span><div>This section will be added in a later phase.</div></div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>

  <!-- Full-width repeating footer, pinned below the page content -->
